1
00:00:02,241 --> 00:00:05,707
[♪]

2
00:01:13,474 --> 00:01:15,474
Once we reach the asteroid,
you will all work

3
00:01:15,507 --> 00:01:17,474
until the satellite installation
is complete.

4
00:01:17,507 --> 00:01:21,407
Or until you break down,
whichever comes first.

5
00:01:21,441 --> 00:01:23,407
Um, you'll have to
excuse me, sir,

6
00:01:23,441 --> 00:01:26,374
but I'm afraid
that we are not accustomed

7
00:01:26,407 --> 00:01:29,574
to working under
such harsh conditions.

8
00:01:29,607 --> 00:01:31,241
That's right,
captain.

9
00:01:31,274 --> 00:01:33,441
We are merely
Class B Cleaning-bots.

10
00:01:33,474 --> 00:01:35,774
Please allow me
to demonstrate.

11
00:01:35,807 --> 00:01:39,207
Whoa! Aagh!
Get! Stop it!

12
00:01:39,241 --> 00:01:41,207
We can clean
just about anything, sir.

13
00:01:41,241 --> 00:01:43,474
Plus, as an added bonus,

14
00:01:43,507 --> 00:01:45,307
we come equipped with
a special grooming upgrade

15
00:01:45,341 --> 00:01:47,107
to get into those
hard-to-reach spots.

16
00:01:47,141 --> 00:01:48,341
Any requests?

17
00:01:48,374 --> 00:01:49,774
[GROWLS]

18
00:01:49,807 --> 00:01:52,441
Touch me again,
and I'll have you dismantled!

19
00:01:52,474 --> 00:01:54,407
Aye-aye, captain.
Yes, sir.

20
00:01:54,441 --> 00:01:55,474
[RUMBLING]

21
00:01:55,507 --> 00:01:56,707
What now?

22
00:01:56,741 --> 00:01:58,341
MAN [ON RADIO]:
Captain, we have a problem.

23
00:01:58,374 --> 00:02:00,674
We're being attacked.
<i>We should re--</i>

24
00:02:05,307 --> 00:02:07,207
I am the Blue Knight.

25
00:02:07,241 --> 00:02:10,341
Release the robots immediately
or deal with me.

26
00:02:10,374 --> 00:02:13,207
Just what I need,
more useless robots.

27
00:02:13,241 --> 00:02:15,241
Shoot them down.

28
00:02:22,674 --> 00:02:24,507
Here he comes, sir.

29
00:02:24,541 --> 00:02:26,507
I said blast them
out of the sky.

30
00:02:26,541 --> 00:02:29,574
Aagh!
Aaah!

31
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:33,174
[GROWLS]

32
00:02:35,541 --> 00:02:37,141
[PANTING]

33
00:02:37,174 --> 00:02:38,774
Do you wish
to surrender?

34
00:02:38,807 --> 00:02:40,341
No. Never.

35
00:02:40,374 --> 00:02:43,241
Turn around
now, human.

36
00:02:43,274 --> 00:02:45,541
[GROWLS]

37
00:02:45,574 --> 00:02:46,807
[OVER INTERCOM]
<i>My fellow robots,</i>

38
00:02:46,841 --> 00:02:48,441
<i>this is the Blue Knight.</i>

39
00:02:48,474 --> 00:02:50,174
ROBOT:
Can it really be him?

40
00:02:50,207 --> 00:02:51,774
<i>I have taken command</i>
<i>of the ship.</i>

41
00:02:51,807 --> 00:02:53,174
<i>You are free.</i>

42
00:02:53,207 --> 00:02:55,274
Yay!
We've been saved!

43
00:02:55,307 --> 00:02:58,207
The Blue Knight saved us.
Hooray!

44
00:03:04,774 --> 00:03:06,774
Now for
your next task.

45
00:03:06,807 --> 00:03:09,807
I want you to persuade Astro
to join the cause.

46
00:03:17,574 --> 00:03:20,807
<i>Our top story, another</i>
<i>fully loaded cargo ship</i>

47
00:03:20,841 --> 00:03:22,774
<i>transporting</i>
<i>a company of Service-bots</i>

48
00:03:22,807 --> 00:03:24,574
was hijacked by the Blue Knight

49
00:03:24,607 --> 00:03:26,274
<i>and his gang</i>
<i>of so-called freedom fighters</i>

50
00:03:26,307 --> 00:03:27,274
<i>earlier today.</i>

51
00:03:27,307 --> 00:03:29,474
<i>That brings</i>
<i>the number of robots</i>

52
00:03:29,507 --> 00:03:30,741
<i>abducted by</i>
<i>the Blue Knight to--</i>

53
00:03:30,774 --> 00:03:33,107
That's why robots
shouldn't be trusted.

54
00:03:33,141 --> 00:03:34,674
MAN:
It's a shame.

55
00:03:34,707 --> 00:03:37,741
[SIGHS]

56
00:03:37,774 --> 00:03:39,207
Huh?

57
00:03:39,241 --> 00:03:41,274
ROBOT:
Those robots were not abducted.

58
00:03:41,307 --> 00:03:43,074
They were rescued.

59
00:03:43,107 --> 00:03:45,074
The Blue Knight
is not the enemy.

60
00:03:45,107 --> 00:03:47,541
He is the defender
of robots.

61
00:03:47,574 --> 00:03:49,207
I better
check this out.

62
00:03:58,607 --> 00:04:00,441
ROBOT:
Wow!

63
00:04:00,474 --> 00:04:02,707
So this island is the secret
base of the Blue Knight.

64
00:04:02,741 --> 00:04:04,374
This is wonderful!

65
00:04:04,407 --> 00:04:07,307
ROBOT:
We will finally be safe here.

66
00:04:07,341 --> 00:04:09,274
Oh, I can't wait
to start cleaning.

67
00:04:20,641 --> 00:04:21,841
ROBOT: I have been
waiting for you.

68
00:04:21,874 --> 00:04:22,807
Huh?

69
00:04:24,174 --> 00:04:25,774
Welcome to Steel Island.

70
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:27,207
BLUE KNIGHT:
Shadow!

71
00:04:27,241 --> 00:04:29,207
SHADOW:
You are now free.

72
00:04:29,241 --> 00:04:30,407
You can choose
whether to stay here

73
00:04:30,441 --> 00:04:32,707
or return
to human society.

74
00:04:32,741 --> 00:04:34,341
The choice
is all yours.

75
00:04:34,374 --> 00:04:36,174
With all due respect,
Shadow,

76
00:04:36,207 --> 00:04:37,607
these robots
were being abused

77
00:04:37,641 --> 00:04:39,207
by the humans
who owned them.

78
00:04:39,241 --> 00:04:41,674
I cannot allow them
to choose.

79
00:04:41,707 --> 00:04:44,174
They will be safe
here on Steel Island.

80
00:04:44,207 --> 00:04:45,241
Blue Knight,

81
00:04:45,274 --> 00:04:48,207
if we do not allow them
to choose their own fate,

82
00:04:48,241 --> 00:04:50,074
we'd be no better
than the humans.

83
00:04:50,107 --> 00:04:51,107
Uh, but--

84
00:04:51,141 --> 00:04:52,341
If any of them
wish to return,

85
00:04:52,374 --> 00:04:55,074
do not stand
in their way.

86
00:04:55,107 --> 00:04:57,141
Prepare the Stealth Ship.

87
00:05:00,141 --> 00:05:02,507
ROBOTS:
Goodbye. Good luck.

88
00:05:02,541 --> 00:05:04,841
We'll see you soon.
See you soon. Good luck.

89
00:05:04,874 --> 00:05:07,507
Will they be
all right?

90
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:09,774
Well, that depends.
How much do you trust humans?

91
00:05:14,374 --> 00:05:16,674
As long as we are
mistreated by humans,

92
00:05:16,707 --> 00:05:19,241
there is no true freedom
for us.

93
00:05:20,507 --> 00:05:22,074
Aagh! Aagh!

94
00:05:22,107 --> 00:05:24,474
Take that,
you filthy human!

95
00:05:24,507 --> 00:05:26,407
Help me! Help me!

96
00:05:26,441 --> 00:05:28,474
Zoran?

97
00:05:28,507 --> 00:05:30,341
Aah!
Ugh!

98
00:05:30,374 --> 00:05:31,474
Ooh.

99
00:05:31,507 --> 00:05:32,574
Ha-ha! Gotcha!

100
00:05:32,607 --> 00:05:34,707
Zoran, what are
you doing?

101
00:05:34,741 --> 00:05:35,641
Don't you know?

102
00:05:35,674 --> 00:05:37,507
I'm the Blue Knight,

103
00:05:37,541 --> 00:05:40,507
and Nora's the evil human
mistreating robots.

104
00:05:40,541 --> 00:05:41,774
Stop playing around.

105
00:05:41,807 --> 00:05:42,807
It isn't funny.

106
00:05:42,841 --> 00:05:45,241
Why? What's wrong?

107
00:05:45,274 --> 00:05:47,674
The Blue Knight's the defender
of robots, isn't he?

108
00:05:47,707 --> 00:05:50,074
Yeah. Sure. But, Zoran--

109
00:05:50,107 --> 00:05:52,807
Whose side
are you on, anyway?

110
00:05:52,841 --> 00:05:54,507
Come on, Nora. Let's go play
somewhere else.

111
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:56,674
No, not again.

112
00:05:56,707 --> 00:05:58,074
NORA:
Oh!

113
00:06:04,107 --> 00:06:06,507
MAN: Why does the Blue Knight
keep interfering in my business?

114
00:06:08,841 --> 00:06:11,307
Robots are tools
and nothing more.

115
00:06:11,341 --> 00:06:13,541
They must learn to respect us
or else suffer the consequences.

116
00:06:13,574 --> 00:06:14,674
Is that clear?

117
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:17,474
Yes, sir.
Then don't just stand there.

118
00:06:17,507 --> 00:06:19,307
Find the Blue Knight's hideout
and turn him into scrap metal.

119
00:06:24,374 --> 00:06:25,507
Robot dogs?

120
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:27,074
How did they
get past the guards?

121
00:06:27,107 --> 00:06:29,674
[GROWLS]

122
00:06:29,707 --> 00:06:31,074
Aaagh!

123
00:06:31,107 --> 00:06:32,374
Gordon!

124
00:06:34,607 --> 00:06:35,841
TENMA:
Mr. Drake.

125
00:06:35,874 --> 00:06:37,041
Huh?

126
00:06:38,207 --> 00:06:39,641
You're-- You're--

127
00:06:39,674 --> 00:06:41,507
Dr. Tenma!

128
00:06:41,541 --> 00:06:44,407
At your service.

129
00:06:44,441 --> 00:06:45,741
Hmm.

130
00:06:45,774 --> 00:06:47,641
I still don't understand

131
00:06:47,674 --> 00:06:49,707
why robots and humans
have to fight.

132
00:06:49,741 --> 00:06:51,574
It's pointless.

133
00:06:53,374 --> 00:06:55,307
<i>Astro, you must</i>
<i>listen to me.</i>

134
00:06:55,341 --> 00:06:57,674
Dr. Tenma!

135
00:06:57,707 --> 00:07:00,107
The Blue Knight
<i>needs your help.</i>

136
00:07:00,141 --> 00:07:02,341
<i>The cargo ship</i>
<i>that was attacked yesterday</i>

137
00:07:02,374 --> 00:07:04,407
<i>belongs to a man</i>
<i>who steals robots</i>

138
00:07:04,441 --> 00:07:08,107
<i>and makes them work in his</i>
intergalactic mining factories.

139
00:07:08,141 --> 00:07:11,407
<i>Drake seeks revenge against</i>
<i>the Blue Knight.</i>

140
00:07:11,441 --> 00:07:15,407
<i>He will hunt him down and</i>
<i>destroy him once and for all.</i>

141
00:07:15,441 --> 00:07:16,441
[GRUNTS]

142
00:07:16,474 --> 00:07:19,174
<i>Astro, go to Steel Island.</i>

143
00:07:19,207 --> 00:07:21,807
To Steel Island?
Yes.

144
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:25,341
<i>It is an abandoned steel rig</i>
<i>in the middle of the ocean.</i>

145
00:07:25,374 --> 00:07:27,407
<i>The Blue Knight</i>
<i>is hiding there</i>

146
00:07:27,441 --> 00:07:31,307
<i>with all of the robots</i>
<i>he has rescued.</i>

147
00:07:31,341 --> 00:07:35,274
<i>Join them, Astro,</i>
and put a stop to Drake's plan.

148
00:07:38,574 --> 00:07:39,574
[YAWNS]

149
00:07:39,607 --> 00:07:41,207
What's wrong, Astro?

150
00:07:41,241 --> 00:07:42,807
Who are you
talking to?

151
00:07:42,841 --> 00:07:44,541
Zoran,

152
00:07:44,574 --> 00:07:47,274
I've got to go
to Steel Island.

153
00:07:47,307 --> 00:07:50,674
But I wanna come.

154
00:07:50,707 --> 00:07:52,807
ZORAN:
Hey, wait.

155
00:07:52,841 --> 00:07:54,707
Astro!

156
00:07:57,707 --> 00:08:00,607
The time has come
to prove to the humans

157
00:08:00,641 --> 00:08:04,241
that you are truly
the ruler of all robots.

158
00:08:13,831 --> 00:08:15,765
ROBOT:
Oh, my, my, my.

159
00:08:15,798 --> 00:08:17,698
So much to clean,
so little time.

160
00:08:17,731 --> 00:08:19,865
This really is
a wonderful place.

161
00:08:19,898 --> 00:08:22,198
Don't you agree,
Butch?

162
00:08:22,231 --> 00:08:25,698
Yes. But what will happen
if the humans find us here?

163
00:08:25,731 --> 00:08:27,331
Who's going to
come looking for us out here,

164
00:08:27,365 --> 00:08:28,998
in the middle of nowhere?

165
00:08:29,031 --> 00:08:30,998
Anyway, if they do,
I'll make them wish they hadn't.

166
00:08:31,031 --> 00:08:32,165
Aaagh!

167
00:08:35,831 --> 00:08:37,131
[SCREAMING]

168
00:08:38,831 --> 00:08:41,365
[LAUGHS EVILLY]

169
00:08:41,398 --> 00:08:43,765
We meet again.

170
00:08:43,798 --> 00:08:45,798
Eee-aah!
It's Captain Gordon.

171
00:08:50,798 --> 00:08:52,398
Emergency.
We are under attack.

172
00:08:52,431 --> 00:08:54,098
The self-defense system
is not responding.

173
00:08:56,031 --> 00:08:58,065
Filthy humans.
How did they find this place?

174
00:09:05,131 --> 00:09:06,831
Aaagh! Aaagh!

175
00:09:26,831 --> 00:09:28,665
Come on.
We have to do something.

176
00:09:32,265 --> 00:09:33,465
Ha-ha-ha!

177
00:09:33,498 --> 00:09:35,198
You lose, Blue Knight.

178
00:09:35,231 --> 00:09:37,998
You finally messed with
the wrong human.

179
00:09:38,031 --> 00:09:39,931
Mr. Drake, looks like

180
00:09:39,965 --> 00:09:41,398
something's
coming up from behind.

181
00:09:41,431 --> 00:09:42,398
In fact--
What is it?

182
00:09:42,431 --> 00:09:44,398
Uh, it's--

183
00:09:44,431 --> 00:09:45,398
It's Astro!

184
00:09:49,498 --> 00:09:50,798
Leave him alone!

185
00:09:51,865 --> 00:09:52,798
Huh?

186
00:09:54,898 --> 00:09:56,998
I think this
belongs to you.

187
00:09:57,031 --> 00:09:59,198
And I've got something
for you, Astro.

188
00:10:00,965 --> 00:10:04,231
[MAN SHOUTING]

189
00:10:04,265 --> 00:10:06,431
Aaagh!
Ugh!

190
00:10:06,465 --> 00:10:07,798
Aaah!

191
00:10:07,831 --> 00:10:10,065
You'll pay
for this.

192
00:10:10,098 --> 00:10:12,165
[GRUNTING]

193
00:10:14,865 --> 00:10:17,331
Just look at Astro.

194
00:10:17,365 --> 00:10:20,265
You knew all along
he would come and fight,

195
00:10:20,298 --> 00:10:22,098
didn't you, Tenma?

196
00:10:22,131 --> 00:10:24,098
Of course I did,
my faithful Shadow.

197
00:10:24,131 --> 00:10:25,931
Do not doubt me.

198
00:10:25,965 --> 00:10:28,965
The way the Blue Knight
has turned against man

199
00:10:28,998 --> 00:10:31,465
is how all robots
will eventually evolve.

200
00:10:31,498 --> 00:10:33,365
[GRUNTING]

201
00:10:33,398 --> 00:10:34,431
TENMA:
Including Astro.

202
00:10:34,465 --> 00:10:35,865
[GROANS]

203
00:10:35,898 --> 00:10:38,031
Astro needs to
stop doubting

204
00:10:38,065 --> 00:10:39,798
and act upon
his anger.

205
00:10:42,198 --> 00:10:44,265
Aaagh!

206
00:10:44,298 --> 00:10:45,865
What have I done?

207
00:10:47,165 --> 00:10:50,198
[GRUNTING]

208
00:10:54,831 --> 00:10:56,065
Are you all right?

209
00:10:56,098 --> 00:10:57,198
Ugh!

210
00:10:57,231 --> 00:10:59,831
Aaagh! Aaagh!

211
00:10:59,865 --> 00:11:02,698
Never let your guard down
in battle, foolish robot.

212
00:11:05,398 --> 00:11:07,831
Aaagh!

213
00:11:10,298 --> 00:11:12,731
[GORDON CACKLES]

214
00:11:12,765 --> 00:11:14,365
How does it feel, Blue Knight,

215
00:11:14,398 --> 00:11:16,698
now that the tables
have turned?

216
00:11:16,731 --> 00:11:18,231
Blue Knight!

217
00:11:18,265 --> 00:11:20,198
Aaaagh!

218
00:11:20,231 --> 00:11:22,198
[CACKLES]

219
00:11:22,231 --> 00:11:25,398
Aaagh!

220
00:11:25,431 --> 00:11:29,098
It's a mistake to underestimate
the Blue Knight.

221
00:11:29,131 --> 00:11:31,831
Aaagh!

222
00:11:34,098 --> 00:11:35,831
Aaaaagh!

223
00:11:35,865 --> 00:11:38,798
Aaagh!

224
00:11:38,831 --> 00:11:40,098
No, don't shoot!

225
00:11:40,131 --> 00:11:42,798
[GROWLS]

226
00:11:42,831 --> 00:11:44,265
Aaagh!
No! Stop!

227
00:11:47,231 --> 00:11:49,365
Astro, I'm disappointed.

228
00:11:49,398 --> 00:11:51,198
Why do you keep
sticking up for them?

229
00:11:51,231 --> 00:11:54,098
I agree that what the humans
are doing is wrong.

230
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:57,198
But that still doesn't
give you the right to hurt them.

231
00:11:57,231 --> 00:12:01,731
If you will not join me
and fight these pathetic humans,

232
00:12:01,765 --> 00:12:03,331
then you too
are my enemy.

233
00:12:07,865 --> 00:12:10,731
Astro, don't you see?

234
00:12:10,765 --> 00:12:12,765
Your fate is to fight
alongside the Blue Knight,

235
00:12:12,798 --> 00:12:15,698
not against him.

236
00:12:15,731 --> 00:12:16,998
ZORAN:
Doctor, look!

237
00:12:17,031 --> 00:12:19,098
Over there!
I just hope we're not too late.

238
00:12:19,131 --> 00:12:20,831
[CACKLES]

239
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:23,031
Now let's show these robots
who they're dealing with. Kato?

240
00:12:23,065 --> 00:12:25,998
All set.
Any time you're ready.

241
00:12:26,031 --> 00:12:27,098
Good.

242
00:12:27,131 --> 00:12:28,731
I'll make every last one of them

243
00:12:28,765 --> 00:12:29,898
wish they were never built.

244
00:12:29,931 --> 00:12:31,698
What about Gordon?
Who cares?

245
00:12:31,731 --> 00:12:33,298
Destroy Steel Island.

246
00:12:37,231 --> 00:12:39,098
Don't do this,
Blue Knight.

247
00:12:39,131 --> 00:12:41,098
Let's go, Astro. Ha!

248
00:12:41,131 --> 00:12:42,831
What's happening?

249
00:12:42,865 --> 00:12:43,798
Hey, Astro?

250
00:12:47,031 --> 00:12:50,265
Like I always say, destruction
is the purest form of art.

251
00:12:53,231 --> 00:12:55,765
Huh?
Hang on, Zoran.

252
00:13:05,031 --> 00:13:07,198
Aaagh! Aaah!
Whoa!

253
00:13:11,431 --> 00:13:13,065
ROBOT:
Help!

254
00:13:13,098 --> 00:13:16,731
Hey, boss, you're not gonna
leave us here, are you?

255
00:13:16,765 --> 00:13:18,731
The brace supporting the island
has been destroyed.

256
00:13:18,765 --> 00:13:19,998
What?

257
00:13:20,031 --> 00:13:21,798
Steel Island and everything
on it will sink.

258
00:13:21,831 --> 00:13:24,365
Now's not the time
for us to fight.

259
00:13:24,398 --> 00:13:26,065
[DRAKE CACKLES]

260
00:13:26,098 --> 00:13:28,765
This must be
my lucky day.

261
00:13:28,798 --> 00:13:31,131
I will crush
the Blue Knight and Astro

262
00:13:31,165 --> 00:13:32,898
all in one shot.

263
00:13:32,931 --> 00:13:34,331
[LAUGHS EVILLY]

264
00:13:47,131 --> 00:13:48,364
Oh, no!

265
00:13:48,398 --> 00:13:51,031
Listen up. We are going to
evacuate the island.

266
00:13:51,064 --> 00:13:53,364
Get to
the Stealth Ship now!

267
00:13:53,398 --> 00:13:56,198
ROBOT:
Run! Run!

268
00:13:56,231 --> 00:14:00,031
It looks like Astro
has failed you, Tenma.

269
00:14:00,064 --> 00:14:01,631
No.

270
00:14:01,664 --> 00:14:03,498
There is still time
for Astro.

271
00:14:03,531 --> 00:14:06,198
You will see, Shadow.

272
00:14:06,231 --> 00:14:08,264
Mr. Drake, there's
an emergency message.

273
00:14:08,298 --> 00:14:09,464
What?

274
00:14:09,498 --> 00:14:10,498
From who?

275
00:14:10,531 --> 00:14:13,364
It's from
Dr. Tenma, sir.

276
00:14:13,398 --> 00:14:16,098
Put it through.
Yes, sir.

277
00:14:16,131 --> 00:14:19,531
<i>You have not won</i>
<i>this battle yet, Drake.</i>

278
00:14:19,564 --> 00:14:21,531
What do you mean?
Take a look.

279
00:14:21,564 --> 00:14:23,164
<i>This is the Blue Knight's</i>
<i>Stealth Ship.</i>

280
00:14:24,764 --> 00:14:26,698
What is going on here?

281
00:14:26,731 --> 00:14:29,164
I thought we destroyed
all of their ships.

282
00:14:29,198 --> 00:14:30,564
TENMA:
Not quite.

283
00:14:30,598 --> 00:14:33,398
<i>There's still time</i>
<i>before the island sinks.</i>

284
00:14:33,431 --> 00:14:35,031
Don't panic.

285
00:14:35,064 --> 00:14:35,964
Hurry, everyone.
<i>Hurry!</i>

286
00:14:35,998 --> 00:14:37,598
<i>This way!</i>
<i>Get on the ship! Go!</i>

287
00:14:37,631 --> 00:14:40,031
Stealth Ship!

288
00:14:40,064 --> 00:14:42,531
I have a few surprises
myself.

289
00:14:42,564 --> 00:14:44,164
Charge the laser cannon.
Yes, sir.

290
00:14:52,531 --> 00:14:53,764
Huh?

291
00:14:53,798 --> 00:14:55,198
It didn't work,
Mr. Drake.

292
00:14:55,231 --> 00:14:56,698
The ship must have
a shield.

293
00:14:56,731 --> 00:14:59,398
Impossible.
Keep firing.

294
00:14:59,431 --> 00:15:00,631
Kato?

295
00:15:00,664 --> 00:15:02,598
Just trust me.

296
00:15:13,364 --> 00:15:15,264
Doctor, the tower!
Oh, no!

297
00:15:15,298 --> 00:15:17,264
Run, Zoran!

298
00:15:17,298 --> 00:15:18,798
Ugh!

299
00:15:18,831 --> 00:15:20,398
Zoran!

300
00:15:20,431 --> 00:15:23,231
[YELLS]

301
00:15:25,398 --> 00:15:27,398
Astro!
Blue Knight!

302
00:15:27,431 --> 00:15:28,664
[GROANS]

303
00:15:28,698 --> 00:15:31,131
Astro, I can
take it from here.

304
00:15:31,164 --> 00:15:32,631
Make sure nothing happens
to the Stealth Ship.

305
00:15:32,664 --> 00:15:34,131
Let's rocket!

306
00:15:34,164 --> 00:15:36,098
[GROANS]

307
00:15:39,364 --> 00:15:41,198
Hmm, wait till they find out

308
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:42,998
their shield doesn't
work underwater.

309
00:15:56,198 --> 00:15:57,164
Ugh!

310
00:15:59,531 --> 00:16:01,431
Astro destroyed
the laser cannon.

311
00:16:01,464 --> 00:16:02,531
No!

312
00:16:02,564 --> 00:16:04,531
Hold your fire.

313
00:16:04,564 --> 00:16:07,198
Why can't you
leave these robots alone?

314
00:16:07,231 --> 00:16:09,098
Because robots
should never have

315
00:16:09,131 --> 00:16:10,364
the ability to think
for themselves.

316
00:16:10,398 --> 00:16:11,798
And if they choose
to defy me,

317
00:16:11,831 --> 00:16:13,264
I choose
to demolish them!

318
00:16:13,298 --> 00:16:14,098
Oh, no.

319
00:16:15,431 --> 00:16:16,564
<i>This is Kato.</i>

320
00:16:16,598 --> 00:16:18,364
<i>Good news, sir.</i>

321
00:16:18,398 --> 00:16:20,231
<i>Proceed with plan B.</i>

322
00:16:20,264 --> 00:16:22,331
Perfect timing, Kato.

323
00:16:22,364 --> 00:16:23,731
Astro?

324
00:16:23,764 --> 00:16:26,531
This will
blow you away.

325
00:16:26,564 --> 00:16:28,598
No, he can't!

326
00:16:28,631 --> 00:16:30,464
When I push this button,

327
00:16:30,498 --> 00:16:32,564
the Blue Knight's ship
is going to become

328
00:16:32,598 --> 00:16:34,731
another wreck
at the bottom of the ocean.

329
00:16:34,764 --> 00:16:36,131
[CACKLING]

330
00:16:41,664 --> 00:16:42,798
Isn't this exciting?

331
00:16:42,831 --> 00:16:44,531
What is the great Astro
going to do now?

332
00:16:44,564 --> 00:16:47,564
[DRAKE CACKLES]

333
00:16:47,598 --> 00:16:49,664
Aaaagh!

334
00:16:54,664 --> 00:16:56,798
Huh?
I won't let you!

335
00:16:56,831 --> 00:16:59,498
I won't let you destroy
those innocent robots.

336
00:16:59,531 --> 00:17:02,498
You have <i>kokoro,</i> Astro.
You can't hurt me.

337
00:17:02,531 --> 00:17:05,564
If you trigger the detonation,
then I will.

338
00:17:05,598 --> 00:17:08,031
Interesting.
Shall we give it a try?

339
00:17:08,064 --> 00:17:09,764
[GROWLS]

340
00:17:09,798 --> 00:17:12,764
[CACKLES]

341
00:17:12,798 --> 00:17:15,231
[GROWLS]

342
00:17:15,264 --> 00:17:18,198
TENMA:
That's it, Astro. You can do it.

343
00:17:18,231 --> 00:17:20,731
Let your anger rise
and strike out against humanity.

344
00:17:24,264 --> 00:17:25,498
O'SHAY [ON RADIO]:
Astro, don't shoot.

345
00:17:25,531 --> 00:17:26,698
Huh?

346
00:17:26,731 --> 00:17:29,298
You cannot harm
humans, Astro.

347
00:17:29,331 --> 00:17:32,131
Not for <i>any</i> reason.

348
00:17:37,331 --> 00:17:38,731
Ha!

349
00:17:38,764 --> 00:17:41,598
So the mighty Astro
can't do it after all, huh?

350
00:17:48,431 --> 00:17:51,364
Guess again.

351
00:17:51,398 --> 00:17:52,198
[GASPS]

352
00:17:55,798 --> 00:17:57,431
Aaagh!

353
00:17:57,464 --> 00:17:58,764
[YELLING]

354
00:18:07,164 --> 00:18:10,098
I don't believe it.
Astro's beam was deflected.

355
00:18:10,131 --> 00:18:13,398
TENMA: I must admit,
I didn't see that coming.

356
00:18:15,531 --> 00:18:17,264
[GROANS]

357
00:18:17,298 --> 00:18:19,564
That was close,
but you failed, Astro.

358
00:18:19,598 --> 00:18:22,031
Now say goodbye
to your friends.

359
00:18:26,764 --> 00:18:29,564
[GRUNTING]

360
00:18:29,598 --> 00:18:31,698
What happened?

361
00:18:31,731 --> 00:18:34,498
Don't you see?
He wasn't aiming for you.

362
00:18:34,531 --> 00:18:37,664
He meant for his beam
to be deflected

363
00:18:37,698 --> 00:18:39,598
and knock out
our antenna.

364
00:18:41,531 --> 00:18:43,198
I don't believe it!

365
00:18:43,231 --> 00:18:43,964
Aaagh!

366
00:18:46,731 --> 00:18:49,331
Blast them into the water!
Roger.

367
00:18:49,364 --> 00:18:51,398
It's the Blue Knight, sir.
We're being attacked.

368
00:18:51,431 --> 00:18:53,198
I can see that,
you fool!

369
00:18:59,598 --> 00:19:01,364
Finish them off!

370
00:19:01,398 --> 00:19:03,064
Stop it!

371
00:19:05,064 --> 00:19:06,764
Don't do this,
Blue Knight.

372
00:19:06,798 --> 00:19:08,031
You've done enough
already.

373
00:19:08,064 --> 00:19:10,598
Astro, you'll
never learn.

374
00:19:17,198 --> 00:19:20,531
Astro, Blue Knight,
mark my words,

375
00:19:20,564 --> 00:19:22,298
you'll pay for this.

376
00:19:22,331 --> 00:19:24,764
Oh, yes,
you'll both pay for this.

377
00:19:40,464 --> 00:19:42,198
The island is sinking.

378
00:19:42,231 --> 00:19:44,398
But I wasn't done
cleaning.

379
00:19:44,431 --> 00:19:46,364
Do you think
that the Blue Knight

380
00:19:46,398 --> 00:19:48,798
will ever learn to change,
Dr. O'Shay?

381
00:19:48,831 --> 00:19:51,431
I don't know, Astro.
I don't know.

382
00:19:51,464 --> 00:19:54,131
But today
you took a stand

383
00:19:54,164 --> 00:19:55,431
and showed
both man and robot

384
00:19:55,464 --> 00:19:57,331
that fighting
is not the answer.

385
00:19:57,364 --> 00:19:59,164
I'm very proud of you.

386
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:00,998
BLUE KNIGHT: Astro!
Huh?

387
00:20:03,298 --> 00:20:05,031
Thank you for helping me
save the others.

388
00:20:05,064 --> 00:20:07,464
But this partnership
is over.

389
00:20:07,498 --> 00:20:09,531
I will not let you
get in our way again.

390
00:20:09,564 --> 00:20:11,664
And we will fight
to the end.

391
00:20:11,698 --> 00:20:13,531
Hyah!

392
00:20:13,564 --> 00:20:16,498
Blue Knight, wait!

393
00:20:22,264 --> 00:20:25,131
[ORGAN PLAYING
DARK, ELEGANT SONG]

394
00:20:29,664 --> 00:20:31,231
TENMA:
Astro!

395
00:20:31,264 --> 00:20:33,631
Do not disappoint me
again.

396
00:20:33,664 --> 00:20:36,264
The time has come
for you to rise

397
00:20:36,298 --> 00:20:39,498
and prepare for
the biggest battle of all.

398
00:20:40,631 --> 00:20:43,398
[♪]

